Source Resolver
===============================================================================

A source resolver loads Mech source from an address or request.

Sources are Mech code. They may come from files, memory, packages, modules, or another host-provided source system.

1. Source vs resource
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

A resource is a protected runtime object addressed through a provider.

A source is Mech code loaded for parsing, resolving, importing, or running.

Some resources contain source files, but not all resources are sources.

2. Resolver responsibilities
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

A source resolver can:

- Resolve source addresses.
- Load source content.
- Support imports between source files.
- Report missing sources.
- Provide source metadata to the runtime.

3. Default resolver
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The default runtime uses an in-memory source resolver. Hosts can provide other resolvers through runtime construction.
